ChatGPT said:
Perfect! Postman has built-in support for response body schema validation using JavaScript-based tests. You can write a schema validation test in the â€œTestsâ€ tab of Postman for each request.

âœ… Step-by-Step: Validate Response Body Schema in Postman
1. Make your API request
Use the â€œBodyâ€ tab (for POST/PUT), set headers if needed, and hit Send.

2. Go to the "Tests" tab of your request
3. Use the tv4 or ajv validator
Postman includes the tv4 and ajv JSON schema validators.

Hereâ€™s an example using Ajv (recommended â€“ stricter and modern):

ðŸ“„ Example Schema Validation Test
Suppose your response looks like this:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "id": 101,
  "name": "Rithesh",
  "email": "rithesh@example.com",
  "is_active": true
}
Then in the Tests tab, write this:

javascript
Copy
Edit
pm.test("Response schema is valid", function () {
    const schema = {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
            "id": { "type": "number" },
            "name": { "type": "string" },
            "email": { "type": "string", "format": "email" },
            "is_active": { "type": "boolean" }
        },
        "required": ["id", "name", "email", "is_active"]
    };

    pm.response.to.have.jsonSchema(schema);
});
This will validate:

The data type of each field

All required fields are present

ðŸ” Tips:
To test an array of objects, set "type": "array" and use items:

javascript
Copy
Edit
"type": "array",
"items": {
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    ...
  }
}
Postman gives clear schema validation errors in the Test Results if validation fails.